Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.86,0:00:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, another cup of coffee over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.53,0:00:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, the truth is, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.99,0:00:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask of you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.78,0:00:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.24,0:00:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.49,0:00:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.65,0:00:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.65,0:00:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, this would be\Nmy own personal matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.94,0:00:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't really have any\Nbusiness asking you for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.53,0:00:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So will you please hear me out first?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.90,0:01:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as long as I'm just listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.94,0:01:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.90,0:01:17.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.30,0:01:25.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.65,0:01:33.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.52,0:01:38.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.94,0:01:44.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:49.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.83,0:01:54.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.36,0:02:01.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.78,0:02:09.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:14.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.77,0:02:21.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.03,0:02:28.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.45,0:02:41.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.49,0:02:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had an uncle named Sekitani Jun...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.49,0:02:47.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Circumstances of the Classic Lit Club's Scion
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.90,0:02:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I want you to help me remember\Nwhat it was that I heard from my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really following.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.10,0:02:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I'm sorry,\NI'm getting ahead of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.69,0:03:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you through this step by step.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.69,0:03:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it happens, ever since my uncle\Nwent to India seven years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.07,0:03:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he has been missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.24,0:03:11.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese National Missing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.24,0:03:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I was a little girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.58,0:03:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was quite attached to this uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would always answer my questions,\Nno matter how absurd they were,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it was as though there\Nwas nothing he didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.99,0:03:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in kindergarten,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out that my uncle\Nwas in the Classic Lit Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I became interested in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.22,0:03:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was because\Nthe name reminded me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the vinegar kelp that we always had at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:35.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}sukonbu{\i0}: 'vinegar kelp'\N{\i1}Kotenbu{\i0}: 'Classic Lit\NClub'
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, I asked my uncle about something\Nhaving to do with the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the only time he was\Nreluctant to answer, for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reluctant?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.99,0:03:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I threw quite a tantrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.28,0:03:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and finally, my uncle answered me...\Nbut when I heard the answer, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:03:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.03,0:04:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cried. Whether I was scared,\Nor I was sad, I started bawling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.32,0:04:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.49,0:04:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, I startled my mom,\Nand she came dashing in,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.19,0:04:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but my uncle didn't do anything\Nto try to comfort me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.99,0:04:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shock of what happened\Nback then was so great
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.78,0:04:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I don't remember anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.19,0:04:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once I got into middle school,\NI started growing curious about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did my uncle shy away from answering?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't he try to console me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've tried to do everything\NI could since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.36,0:04:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've tried everything in my power\Nto contact the Sekitani family,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.94,0:04:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from whom we are now estranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.57,0:04:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no matter what I do, I can't remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.69,0:05:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, when I enrolled\Nat Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured that the Classic Lit Club\Nwas my last hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.32,0:05:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's what your "personal matter" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I didn't realize that the Classic Lit\NClub was on the verge of being closed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked in the faculty room,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.49,0:05:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there weren't any teachers there who\Nremembered my uncle from 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.50,0:05:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why is it that you're\Nnow turning to me for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.32,0:05:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you seem like you might\Nconclude something that I never imagined!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.28,0:05:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you did with the lock, and the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.78,0:05:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that recruitment note, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.11,0:05:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you will be able to\Nlead me to my answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you giving me too\Nmuch credit. That stuff was just luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please let me rely on that luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.78,0:06:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Chitanda, this is a question which,\Nnot to lay it on too thick,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.78,0:06:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could affect her entire outlook on life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she wants an energy\Nconservationist like me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to take on even the least bit of\N{\i1}that {\i0}kind of responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.82,0:06:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you only asking me?\NSurely there are others you could turn to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could use strength\Nin numbers to tackle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.28,0:06:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you ask some\Nof your friends, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'm not one to go\Naround blabbing about my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not something that I can\Ntalk about with just anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.57,0:06:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.78,0:07:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm asking for quite a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.28,0:07:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that I shouldn't be dragging you\Ninto my memories, too. It's just,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while you may be a lot less\Npersonable than my uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.94,0:07:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you also answered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.86,0:07:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well excuse me for not being personable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I saw my uncle when\NI looked at you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school goes on for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take your time\Nand search during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.49,0:07:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to remember what my uncle\Nsaid before he passes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Passes away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If it's unknown if someone\Nis alive or dead for seven years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that they can\Nbe declared legally dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.11,0:07:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle's family intends to put\Nthis matter to rest at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.07,0:07:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they're going to hold\Na funeral, too... at least a small one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.03,0:08:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why... That's why I want to have\Nwhat my uncle told me in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I'm at his funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.90,0:08:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.57,0:08:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you don't have anything\Nelse you want to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to claim\Nany responsibility over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.15,0:08:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, I'm not saying that\NI agree to your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.40,0:08:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I will keep some mental notes\Nabout what you've told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.28,0:08:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if I come across anything\Nthat might offer any hints,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be sure to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have any trouble with\Nmy explanation, I'll give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:08:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll agree to that,\Nthen I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.28,0:09:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. I greatly\Nlook forward to your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.49,0:09:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.32,0:09:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school life being what it is,\Nthings are never all rosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.24,0:09:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regular examinations, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.50,0:09:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Midterm tests have begun\Nat Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.53,0:09:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the testing period,\Nall club activities are suspended.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.28,0:09:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, that goes for\Nthe Classic Lit Club, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.94,0:09:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we normally don't do anything anyhow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.05,0:09:42.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Library
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.05,0:09:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so honestly, there's not much difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you'd think it would be\Nokay to carry on as always,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.24,0:09:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but since the keys weren't being\Ncirculated, there was nothing we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Term Midterm Schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.82,0:09:57.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Term Midterm Test\NDay 2 2nd Period\NMath I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:09:59.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Term Midterm Test\NDay 3 2nd Period\NWorld History B
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.11,0:10:02.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Term Midterm Test\NDay 4 2nd Period\NIntegrated Science
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.61,0:10:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.40,0:10:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whew...\NIt's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:15.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,1st Term Midterm Schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Midterm tests are done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.16,0:10:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am currently in Istanbul.\NI goofed up a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm stuck here in\Nthe Japanese consulate,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I haven't seen inside the city yet."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do, Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.03,0:10:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This trip has been fun.\NI'm sure that ten years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.49,0:10:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't regret spending this time."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.32,0:10:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"By the way, how's the Classic Lit Club?\NHave any more members?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.07,0:10:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, there's something worrying me,\Nso I thought I'd write you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.90,0:10:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to make an anthology?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.69,0:11:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Classic Lit Club entered an anthology\Neach year for the culture festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.99,0:11:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still doing that? If you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.53,0:11:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that you might\Nnot know how to make one,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since the Classic Lit Club\Nanthologies aren't in the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to look in the club room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.28,0:11:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an unused chemical locker there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.28,0:11:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the back-number anthologies\Nare inside. It's not locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.40,0:11:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, once I reach Pristina,\NI'll give you a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.03,0:11:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sincerely, Oreki Tomoe."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.49,0:11:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A chemical locker?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.90,0:11:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This timing is too good to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:40.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shouman{\i0} ('The Greening')\NWhen nature\Nwaxeth full, and limbs and leaves grow lush
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:40.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.09,0:11:44.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.47,0:11:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.03,0:11:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really. I even brought the letter with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.78,0:11:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it. The chemical locker, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.49,0:11:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:12:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now that you mention it,\NI didn't see one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So where are the anthologies?\NWhere are the anthologies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.44,0:12:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, calm down, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.32,0:12:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.07,0:12:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, the letter just said\Nthe chemical locker in the club room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.90,0:12:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis graduated from here two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, the club room has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.74,0:12:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Oreki, do you know\Nwhere it was two years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.74,0:12:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already asked the adviser.\NIt was the Biology prep room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.86,0:12:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? That's unusually\Nwell-prepared of you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just increasing our efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pumped about this, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.82,0:12:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not. I don't\Ngenerally get "pumped."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.07,0:12:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.74,0:12:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come to think of it,\Nwhere's Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.03,0:12:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Handicrafts Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.53,0:12:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said something about getting\Na head start on the summer fashion scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.01,0:12:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:02.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Biology Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.69,0:13:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.44,0:13:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anyone in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had the door locked. Are you here\Nto join the Wall Newspaper Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not that. Um, this is the\NWall Newspaper Club room, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.74,0:13:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that smell, cologne?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.80,0:13:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, air freshener?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.07,0:13:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, is there something I can do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.61,0:13:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I am Chitanda Eru,\Nthe Classic Lit Club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:14:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Togaito-{\i1}senpai{\i0},\Nfrom Class 3-E, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.74,0:14:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw you at the\NManninbashi home last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.15,0:14:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Manninbashi home? Hold on,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.15,0:14:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you wouldn't happen to be of\Nthe Kanda Chitandas, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.65,0:14:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you for all\Nyou do for my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.90,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, no, I should thank you.\NSo, you're a Chitanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he so distracted?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.36,0:14:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.19,0:14:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, actually, we heard that\Nthe back-number issues
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.11,0:14:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the Classic Lit Club's anthologies\Nare stored here in the Biology prep room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.09,0:14:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This used to be\Nthe Classic Lit Club room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.09,0:14:38.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Biology Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.36,0:14:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, y-yeah. It was back\Nwhen I was a 1st-year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.99,0:14:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then do you know\Nabout the anthologies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.99,0:14:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.99,0:14:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me, but they're\Nsupposedly in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.99,0:14:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let us look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I already said\Nthey weren't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.07,0:15:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.49,0:15:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.65,0:15:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think something's up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then don't just leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.40,0:15:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sorry I can't help you.\NTry somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.44,0:15:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we followed a trail that\Nshows that they're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.15,0:15:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're not here, then we'll\Nhave to search the whole school!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.02,0:15:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole school?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta be kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just need a few moments!\NPlease let us see inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.15,0:15:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to let any\Nnon-club members in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Senpai, before this was a club room,\Nit was a classroom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.03,0:15:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.24,0:15:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Lit Club member, Ibara Mayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.90,0:15:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Fine, go ahead and look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't tear the place up too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:53.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kami High Monthly Newsletter Issue 496
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.15,0:16:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are your other club members?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.40,0:16:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they're off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was brainstorming ideas\Nfor the June issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called the "Kami High Monthly\NNewsletter." It goes way back,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.15,0:16:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we're nearing our 500th issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.94,0:16:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like it's in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.94,0:16:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? Oreki...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.57,0:16:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, when you changed club rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.49,0:16:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you all move anything out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, we carried\Na number of cardboard boxes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.11,0:16:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cardboard boxes, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.74,0:16:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, getting our hands on it\Nis a somewhat difficult problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can trip him up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.40,0:17:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but there are\Nso many things in this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it would take a lot of\Ntrouble to search them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.61,0:17:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get the adviser's help\Nto search everything top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.78,0:17:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can't. I told you I didn't\Nwant you tearing everything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if they aren't here, we don't\Nhave any other leads on them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will be responsible for putting\Neverything back, so please...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.44,0:17:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.49,0:17:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.90,0:17:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.78,0:17:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me any\N"top-to-bottom search" business!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.24,0:17:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not your club room!\NGot it?! Now get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.53,0:17:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, we're just interested in\Nwhat's inside a chemical locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.32,0:17:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.29,0:17:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The anthologies should be inside it.\NAs long as we have those,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.81,0:17:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we won't have to trouble you\Nover anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.69,0:17:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, we have an errand\Nto go run at the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.03,0:18:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After we leave, if you happen\Nto find the anthologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you mind leaving them in the\NEarth Science prep room for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.40,0:18:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door is unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.24,0:18:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saying you what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. If I find them,\Nthat's what I'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.40,0:18:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, 1st-year!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.86,0:18:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never caught your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.11,0:18:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am {\i0}sorry it came to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.07,0:18:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Oreki,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.57,0:18:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why are we waiting out here like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.44,0:18:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're conserving energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.65,0:18:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Chitanda, in what regard\Nis the Togaito family famous?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.78,0:19:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... They have influence\Nover secondary education...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.69,0:19:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their family has a number of\Npeople in educational positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.36,0:19:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Five minutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.86,0:19:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be getting back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.45,0:19:14.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.36,0:19:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The anthologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.23,0:19:24.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.53,0:19:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Oreki! How did you do this?!\NDid you know something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a little intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Intimidation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Ibara, can you keep a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? If you tell me not to\Nsay anything, then I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.57,0:19:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.78,0:19:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, first off,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.99,0:19:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when Togaito left the room,\Nhe was clearly acting wary about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.44,0:19:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.32,0:19:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about inside the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.74,0:20:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window was open,\Nand the fan was running,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.65,0:20:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the way it was pointing, the paper\Non the table was being blown around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.11,0:20:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to air the place out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.40,0:20:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. So, why was he\Nso keen to ventilate the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To go even further,\Nwhy did he lock himself inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even place infrared sensors outside?\NJ-Just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.07,0:20:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, infrared sensors?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.53,0:20:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There were small, strange boxes\Non either side of the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.40,0:20:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposing that thing with the antenna\Non it inside the room was a receiver,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.36,0:20:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if someone were to pass by there,\Nit was rigged to set off an alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.36,0:20:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you would\Nknow something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.19,0:20:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was just inferring\Nfrom the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.65,0:20:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, why would\Nhe take such precautions,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hurry to air out the room\Nwhen someone came too close?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To get rid of a smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.44,0:20:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a reasonable guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.53,0:20:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He also had the smell of\Nair freshener spray at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.74,0:21:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, for what odor would he go to\Nsuch lengths to make sure no one smelled?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's a member of a famous\Nfamily in academic circles,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would mean that he couldn't\Nbe found doing anything illegal,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter what it took.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.24,0:21:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.82,0:21:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, if Chitanda hadn't had her cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.07,0:21:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she would have noticed the\Nsmell at her first breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.79,0:21:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But hold on! Where did the\Nanthologies end up being?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the chemical locker, duh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.65,0:21:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not trying to pull your chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chemical locker had to be\Nunder the makeshift table.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.74,0:21:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably hid his cigarettes\Nand lighter in there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.24,0:21:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, when I asked to\Nsearch the room with the adviser,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.15,0:21:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Togaito panicked the way he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.90,0:21:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really {\i1}are {\i0}weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.86,0:21:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say that to\Nsomeone so typically ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.11,0:21:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh-heh, sunflower!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.24,0:22:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, we found the\Nback-number anthologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.34,0:22:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, so this is what they're like.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.57,0:22:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you go all the way back 40 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.18,0:22:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they really have that hand-made feel\Nabout them. What's the matter, Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.73,0:22:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because they were\Nprinted on a Ditto machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.61,0:22:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or more precisely, it's called\Nmimeograph printing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.07,0:22:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it was invented during the\NMeiji period. What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.74,0:22:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't have copy machines\Nin schools during the 1970s, after all.\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.15,0:22:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? They used copiers for these.\NCome here...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.61,0:22:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What issue is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.36,0:22:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:39.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hyouka{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:41.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Issue 2
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Issue 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.03,0:22:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I found back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.57,0:22:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took it to my uncle,\Nand asked him what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.61,0:22:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.74,0:22:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look inside here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.78,0:23:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This has something about my uncle inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.78,0:23:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something happened here,\N45 years ago, in the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.36,0:23:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This year, once again,\Nculture festival time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.86,0:23:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been a year since\NSekitani-{\i1}senpai {\i0}left.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this last year, he has gone\Nfrom being a hero to a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.28,0:23:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The conflicts, the sacrifices,\Nand even his smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.53,0:23:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are all being swept away\Nto the far reaches of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.54,0:23:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it is for the best.\NThey should not be remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.49,0:23:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For none of that is to be\Nfound in a heroic tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.55,0:23:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the subjectiveness is falling away,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.90,0:23:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as it becomes a classic in the distance\Nof historical perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.90,0:23:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, we in the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.53,0:23:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will also become classics\Nto someone in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.40,0:23:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,October 13, 1968, Koriyama Yoko."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.90,0:23:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "last year" they mention\Nin here would be 45 years ago now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.28,0:24:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that the Classic Lit Club's\NSekitani-{\i1}senpai {\i0}must be my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.33,0:24:07.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani-{\i1}senpai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.90,0:24:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer that my uncle gave to me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had to do with the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.19,0:24:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then everything should be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.03,0:24:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still can't remember. It's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.07,0:24:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so close, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.80,0:24:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it that my uncle\Ntold me that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.56,0:24:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly happened\Nto my uncle 45 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.11,0:24:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just have to look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.28,0:24:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it says that it\Nshouldn't be remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.61,0:24:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I look into it,\Nit might prove unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.28,0:24:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some truths that are\Nbetter off forgotten, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.28,0:24:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they're 45 years in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.61,0:24:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.53,0:25:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are. It's written\Nright here, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.82,0:25:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it is becoming a classic\Nin the distance of historical perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.28,0:25:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning there's a statute of limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.74,0:25:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.78,0:25:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, when I say look into it,\NIssue 2 here talks about "last year,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.44,0:25:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you just have to check out the\Nfirst issue... Hey, what is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.82,0:25:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first issue is the\Nonly one we're missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.03,0:25:37.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.99,0:25:41.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.74,0:25:45.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.74,0:25:51.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.20,0:26:11.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.04,0:26:22.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.47,0:26:28.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.97,0:26:34.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.36,0:26:40.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.07,0:26:45.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.07,0:26:48.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.12,0:26:51.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.82,0:26:55.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.86,0:27:01.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.57,0:27:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Classic Lit\NClub's Glorious Days of Yore."
